.TH "usb_add_function" 9 "usb_add_function" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
usb_add_function \- add a function to a configuration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" usb_add_function
.BI "(struct usb_configuration *config "  ","
.BI "struct usb_function *function "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "config" 12
the configuration
.IP "function" 12
the function being added
.SH "CONTEXT"
single threaded during gadget setup
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
After initialization, each configuration must have one or more
functions added to it.  Adding a function involves calling its \fI\fP\fBbind\fP
method to allocate resources such as interface and string identifiers
and endpoints.

This function returns the value of the function's \fBbind\fP, which is
zero for success else a negative errno value.
